Vanity height is defined by the Council on Tall Buildings and Urban Habitat as the height difference between 
a skyscraper's pinnacle and the highest usable floor (usually observatory, office, restaurant, retail or hotel/residential

Because the CTBUH ranks the world's tallest buildings by height to pinnacle, a number of buildings appear higher 
in the rankings than they otherwise would due to extremely long spires.

The current world's tallest building, Burj Khalifa, is officially 828 meters 

